Architecture plan for Issue #25: Change the app background to a colourful gradient

Project shape:
- Single-page Vite + React + TypeScript frontend application.
- App shell lives in src/App.tsx and renders the full-screen <main> container around CalculatorCard.
- Calculator logic is isolated in src/calculator/* and should not be touched for this visual-only issue.
- Presentational calculator pieces live in src/components/*; the background outside the card is controlled at the app shell level.
- Styling uses Tailwind utility classes directly in JSX, with global Tailwind setup in src/index.css and tailwind.config.js.

Implementation plan:
- Implement Issue #25 by updating the <main> className in src/App.tsx from the current solid background utility to a colourful Tailwind gradient, e.g. bg-gradient-to-br with multiple colour stops.
- Keep layout classes, spacing, text colour, calculator behavior hooks, and component props unchanged.
- Avoid dependency, build config, route, deployment, or shared type changes.

Testing/validation plan:
- Run npm run build to verify TypeScript and Vite production compilation.
- Run npm run test:unit to ensure the visual shell change does not regress calculator behavior or component rendering.
- Existing tests do not assert the exact background colour, so no test fixture changes should be required unless a new visual assertion is intentionally added.

Issue dependency notes:
- Only Issue #25 is in scope, so there are no inter-issue dependencies.
- The change is a one-surface UI styling update in src/App.tsx.
